<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Prince     06-24 0167</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Prince,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Prince Launching European Tour In Paris Next Month</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rock star Prince will be in Europe next
month, and he's bringing 90 people and 100 tons of equipment along
for the trip, a spokesman says.
   Prince plans to begin his European tour with four performances
beginning July 8 in Paris, Bob Merlis, vice president of publicity
for Warner Bros., said Thursday.
   Concerts will follow in Milan, Italy; Antwerp, Belgium; London;
Helsinki, Finland; Stockholm, Sweden; Rotterdam, the Netherlands;
Copenhagen, Denmark, and Modena, Italy, Merlis said. More dates may
be added.
   Prince will perform in the round, with an elaborate stage
featuring three or four settings controlled by hydraulics, Merlis
said.
   He'll be taking 100 tons of stage equipment, and the tour
entourage of 90 people will include a 50-member technical crew, the
spokesman said.
   Prince, who toured Europe last year, plans to begin a U.S. tour
in mid-September, followed by a tour of the Far East, probably in
December and January, Merlis said.
</TEXT>
