   Spain's King Juan Carlos and Queen Sofia headed
home for Spain after a 1{-day rest stop here.
   The royal couple received the traditional flower leis from
military and civilian dignitaries at Hickam Air Force Base before
boarding a Boeing 707 jetliner Thursday.
   They arrived here early Wednesday after an 11-day official visit
to Australia and New Zealand. The king and queen stayed at the
Kahala Hilton.
   The royal couple are scheduled to arrive in Madrid early
Saturday after a refueling stop in Canada.
