<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Philippines-Earthquake     06-24 0101</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Philippines-Earthquake,0104</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Strong Earthquake Recorded In Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake was recorded today in the
Luzon Strait 322 miles north of Manila, the Hong Kong observatory
reported.
   The observatory had no additional details on the quake which
struck at 10:08 a.m. and had a preliminary reading of 5.1 on the
Richter scale.
   The open-ended Richter scale measures ground motion as recorded
on seismographs. Every increase of one number means a ten-fold
increase in intensity.
   An earthquake of magnitude 5 can cause considerable damage in
populated areas, while one of the magnitude 6 can cause severe
damage.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
