seized by a mob and caught in a blazing tyre in the first reported
killing of this kind in Kenya, a newspaper reported today.
   Some residents of the poor Nairobi suburb of Kariobangi grabbed
the man Thursday because they believed he had burgled their houses,
The Standard newspaper said.
   The paper carried a page-one photograph of the victim's charred
remains.
   Mob justice is common in Kenya, but police said it was the first
time they knew of someone being killed with a burning tire.
   The practice is known as ``necklacing.''
