<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--NuclearTest     06-24 0128</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Nuclear Test,0131</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>French Detonate Nuclear Device At Mururoa Atoll</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANBERRA, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   France conducted its second
underground nuclear test in a week at the Mururoa atoll testing
ground in the South Pacific early Friday, officials said.
   The force of the blast was equivalent to about 20,000 tons of
dynamite, said a statement by the Australian Seismological Center
at the Bureau of Mineral Resources.
   An explosion at the atoll June 17 was equivalent to about 6,000
tons, the center said.
   Friday's blast was the fourth on the atoll this year and the
99th in a series started in 1976 when France abandoned atmospheric
testing.
   France maintains a policy of not commenting on reports of its
nuclear tests, which are vigorously opposed by nations in the
region.
</TEXT>
