<HEAD>Walter Matthau's Wife Penning Hollywood Book</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Carol Matthau never told her husband, Walter,
when she finally decided to make her dream come true.
   ``I never said a word about it to him. (I) just started
writing,'' Mrs. Matthau says in the July-August issue of Lear's
magazine.
   Mrs. Matthau, an actress who was twice married to playwright
William Saroyan before her 28-year union with the actor, says her
dream-in-progress is a book about Hollywood called ``The Wrong
Color Green.''
   ``All the cliches about this never-never land are true, yet
nobody has written successfully about it,'' she said. ``There is no
`they' who destroy you here. ... You are your own villain.''
   Mrs. Matthau said she has always been sure that she eventually
would become a writer.
   ``I have 18 hat boxes, beautifully covered in glazed, flowered
chintzes and tied with ribbons, so pretty in my closet, and Walter
thinks I bought 18 hats,'' she said. ``But they are full of little
crumpled papers ... each with a sentence or a phrase that is very
close to me.''
