<HEAD>Two Men Surrender After Taking Four Hostages</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men took four people hostage
in a former soccer star's apartment but surrendered after six hours
of negotiations, police said.
   The two men took the four people hostage Thursday and demanded
nearly $1 million in ransom and a helicopter, police said.
   Authorities said the men threatened to kill their hostages, who
included Teresa Sodre, an actress and wife of Carlos Alberto
Torres, captain of Brazil's national soccer team when it won the
