<HEAD>Woman Charged In Death Of Man She Met Through Personals Ad</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who answered a personal ad and
dated the man she met for a month has been charged seven months
later in his shooting death.
   Vivian Collie Hicks is charged with first-degree murder in the
April death of Douglas Gerald Basham. Charged along with Ms. Hicks
on Thursday was Michael Alvin Scales, 21, who police described as
her current boyfriend. They are being held in Rockingham County
Jail without bond.
   ``I would say it had something to do with the relationship
Vivian and Basham had and maybe her getting a new boyfriend,'' said
Rockingham County Sheriff C.D. Vernon.
   Ms. Hicks and Basham met through a Nov. 22, 1987, advertisment
in the Greensboro News & Record and were later featured in story in
the newspaper. They were both from Reidsville, north of Greensboro.
   The couple planned to marry, but Ms. Hicks told the newspaper in
April that she broke the engagement in December.
   In the personals ad, Basham referred to himself as: ``Me-35,
Beard, Caring, Loving, Country Boy at Heart! You-Special in Your
Own Way. Take The Chance To Write. You Might Be Surprised!''
   At the time the two met, Ms. Hicks was married to Danny Gray
Hicks of Madison. She filed for divorce in early December and later
that month took out a warrant against her husband, charging he had
threatened her over the divorce proceedings.
   The charge was found to be frivolous and malicious by a
Rockingham County judge, who ordered Ms. Hicks to pay $52 in court
fees.
   In February, Basham was arrested after Ms. Hicks took out
warrants against him charging him with beating and harassing her.
Basham was found innocent of the charges.
   Later the month, Ms. Hicks voluntarily dismissed the divorce
action, according to records at the Rockingham County Courthouse.
   At the time of Basham's slaying, Ms. Hicks apparently was dating
Scales, said sheriff's Capt. Bob Gray.
   ``What the relationship was is up for grabs,'' Gray said. ``He
(Scales) says they were dating. She denies it.''
