<2ND_LINE>AM-Kitty's Scar,170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kitty: `Want To See My Scar?'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NANTUCKET, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kitty Dukakis, recovering from major
surgery on her spine, peeled off her neck brace Friday and asked
reporters, ``Want to see my scar?''
   Mrs. Dukakis, beginning a short vacation with husband Michael
Dukakis, said she was feeling well three weeks after doctors
operated to correct two disks that were pressing against her spinal
cord.
   She revealed the modest scar across the front of her neck as she
and the likely Democratic presidential nominee chatted with
reporters and photographers who accompanied them to this resort
island.
   She was wearing a scarf around the neck brace, and she was asked
how much time doctors would allow her to go without the collar.
   She started to respond, then said, ``Want to see my scar?''
   As the surprised crowd laughed, she took off the brace. As she
did, the governor asked, ``Any veterans of the Lyndon Johnson
appendectomy?''
   He was referring to the former president who lifted his shirt to
reveal his scar after gall bladder and kidney stone surgery.
</TEXT>
