<TEXT>
   Tons of rocks and earth tumbling down on a
mountain village have forced the suspension of rescue work at the
site of a major landslide that buried at least 100 people alive,
officials said.
   Radio reports late Thursday said villagers heard people crying
for help from underneath the debris.
   The victims, including 30 travelers stranded in a coffeehouse by
an earlier landslide early Thursday, were buried by the major
landslide which swept down on Catak village Thursday afternoon,
according to reports from the northeastern area.
