   Yields on four-year Treasury notes rose in the
government's latest auction to the highest level since before the
October stock market crash.
   The average yield was 8.36 percent on Thursday, up from 7.90
percent at the last auction on March 24.
   It was the highest rate since four-year notes averaged 9.24
percent on Oct. 6. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
8\ percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,963.20.
   A total of $6.75 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$21.2 billion.
