   Gaining stocks outnumbered losers by about 7 to 5 on the NYSE,
with 692 down, 504 up and 507 unchanged. Volume on the Big Board
totaled 75.24 million shares after the first hour.
   The retreat came despite further strength in the dollar, which
benefited prices in the bond market and caused a consequent drop in
