   Analysts said they did not expect aggressive trading on the
aftermath of the market's advance earlier this week and ahead of
the weekend.
   ``The market has had some good gains, and it probably needs a
rest,'' said Hildegarde Zagorski, second vice president at
Prudential-Bache Securities Inc. ``I think there will be some
consolidation.''
   Among the blue-chips, IBM fell ~ to 124~, International Paper
fell \ to 48], and General Motors fell ] to 79{.
   UAL, which jumped 3~ on Thursday, added another 1[ to 95}.
Merrill Lynch reportedly upgraded its recommendation on the stock.
