<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Sunbeam-Oster     06-24 0170</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Sunbeam-Oster,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Allegheny International to Merge Sunbeam, Oster Operations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Allegheny International Inc. said it would
merge the headquarters operations of its flagship Sunbeam and Oster
appliance divisions.
   ``It's way past high time for it to happen,'' said analyst
Gregory Drahuschak of investment firm Butcher & Singer Inc. in
Pittsburgh. ``Their products are so similar.''
   Financial, research and development, engineering and personnel
functions will be combined at Sunbeam's headquarters in Downers
Grove, Ill., the company said Thursday.
   An unspecified number of employees among the 300 people at Oster
headquarters in Milwaukee, Wis., will be laid off, Allegheny
International said.
   Sales staffs will remain independent. None of the manufacturing
plants will be closed.
   The combined business, to be known as Oster-Sunbeam Appliance
Co., will have 3,000 employees at seven locations in the United
States and Mexico.
   Allegheny International plans to change its name to Sunbeam
Corp. The company is reorganizing under Chapter 11 of the U.S.
bankruptcy laws and awaiting results of a proxy contest with
dissident shareholders.
</TEXT>
