<HEAD>Fed Adds Three Firms To Primary Dealers List</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Federal Reserve Bank of New York announced
Friday that it added three securities firms to its list of primary
dealers.
   Dillon, Read & Co.; S.G. Warburg Securities Inc.; and Wertheim
Schroder & Co. were put on the elite list, bringing to 44 the total
number of primary dealers reporting trading data to the Fed daily,
the bank said.
   The bank also said that First Interstate Capital Markets Inc.
withdrew from the list voluntarily.
   Primary dealers market a full range of U.S. government
securities and meet certain standards set by the bank. The New York
Fed conducts dometic open market operations only with primary
dealers.
